	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>millman</b><br /><i>I think it is very different, and pledging allegiance to your country is something vastly different than surrenduring your soul and free thinking to an imaginary being.<br />
<br />
Mill</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I don't think it's very different at all.  There's something very, very wrong with taking little kids and making them do something like that.  A 20 year old is too young to be allowed to drink, a 16 year old is too young to be allowed to have sex, but an 8 year old is old enough not to be allowed, but to be <b>forced</b> to swear their life and their alligence to something they don't really know anything about, not just once but day after day so it's ingrained in their minds.  I find it to be downright VILLAINOUS behavior.<br />
<br />
To you and everyone else that had no problem with the pledge...  I sincerely ask this, not as a flame...  Do even you consider your word to be worth anything?  If you've ever testified in court, did that oath on the bible to tell the truth mean anything to you?  If you're married, did those sacred vows mean anything to you?  If any of you said yes to any of the above... and really meant it... I seriously wanna know how you can condone being forced to perform a pledge on your life hundreds or even thousands of times before you even knew what you were being forced to vow your life to?  It doesn't matter if you now agree as an adult with that declaration because you didn't know when you were made to do it.  Just the fact that you were made to make such a vow day after day as a child, regardless of the cause.  Getting rid of the pledge was the best thing the liberals have accomplished in a very, very long time.<br />
<br />
I don't care about the religious notes in the pledge, I care that both my own word and all vows in general have been cheapened and desecrated by the U.S. government forcing them as a daily ritual.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
