	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Koushirou</b><br /><i>In no way is the pledge a "forced ritual."  Sure, everyday at school, it's said over the announcements, but there's no one here that makes you stand up and say it, else you be shot out back.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Please.  It may be acceptable now to decline, but it sure wasn't when I or probably or any of the rest of you were in school.  I never saw a single person... no teacher, no student, no one not stand up and make that damn oath.  This implies to any kid "this is not optional."  Nobody ever said "this is optional, you can join in if you want or just sit there and gab with your friends."  What part of school was optional?  Was doing your homework optional?  Could you turn down taking a test?  All of this with no reprocussions?  Of course not.  So why would any kid assume that ridiculous pledge was any different?<br />
<br />
Even if they did know they could decline, what makes you think there'd be no reprocussions from the school staff or even their peers for it?  Kids will use any excuse to abuse and berate their fellow students, and I doubt coming off as an America-hating traitor wouldn't qualify for a confrontation with some other kids.  Not to mention the school staff.  These people are horrible people, IMO.  I rank teachers <i>below</i> lawyers and the common criminal on the list of average worthless human beings.  There's a few gems in the rough, but the majority IMO are nazi pond scum.  Example.<br />
