<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Bufr</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Well allow me to examine the pledge as well...<br />
<br />
"We pledge allegiance to the Flag of the United States of America"<br />
<br />
It is not a peice of cloth. It is a symbol of our nation. And in being a symbol it makes perfect sense to pledge to it.<br />
<br />
"and to the republic for which it stands"<br />
<br />
No majority of people on the face of the earth, especially in America, are scumbags. The majority of people are decent and kind. Even if I accept your position that most people are bad how does that free me from my social responsiblities to them? This part of the pledge is a promise to hold your place in society in the face of tragedy, to take part in her governance, basically to be a good citizen. We are not excused from this responsibility by the failing of others. <br />
<br />
"one nation, under god"<br />
<br />
We are one nation. Hell I am an atheist so we can strike the 'under god' thing but to state 2 words make a 'heavy favoritism' towards a majority is silly. Something like 98% percent of people believe in some kind of God I think the last 2% can throw the majority a word or two in the pledge. We are already ahead in the game since we do not believe in invisible men.<br />
<br />
"indivisible with liberty and justice for all"<br />
<br />
This nation now stands completely indivisible. What difference do states make? Does a Texan need my permission to live next door to me? No. State government exist to address the needs of the people of their state. This is wholly right and proper that they do this. Califorians should decide decisions in their state ands each state to its own citizen. If I disagree with a law of an other state I have a disagreement but no division.<br />
<br />
I stand by our justice systems warts and all! I will take a jury trial, assumption of innocence, guarantee of council, and protection from unreasonable search and seizure even when those same guarantees are used to free a guilty man.  <br />
<br />
(Aside, I know of no instance where a pysch eval has turned a trial in a child molester case. I do know that incorrect evaluation have release predators after their time had been served. The ongoing story in SD might be an example.)<br />
<br />
Common ideals of America held almost universally by its citizens...<br />
<br />
We have the right to life.<br />
We have the right to happiness.<br />
We have the right to property.<br />
We have the right to be free.<br />
We believe in the individual.<br />
<br />
You can point out disagreement in the application of these ideals but must leave untouched that they are, in general, held by the people of the nation.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
