We, the citizens, have legalized seizure of property. It has been voted on in a many states and is generally support by the public as a tool against drug dealers and organized crime. I dispute that billions have been stolen from innocent people. He made a statement that 80% came from people who had charges against them dropped. I have not found anything to support this.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>The original page I linked on the matter.  <a href="http://www.lp.org/lpnews/0103/forfeiture.html" target="_blank">http://www.lp.org/lpnews/0103/forfeiture.html</a><br />
<br />
And I quote, " According to the Pittsburgh Press, 80% of seizure victims are never even charged with a crime."  Note that it doesn't even say had the charges dropped.  Charges were never even filed.  Later it was said, "Asset forfeiture is a growth industry. Seizures have increased from $27 million in 1986 to over $644 million in 1991 to over $2 billion today."  80% of 2 billion is 1.6 billion.  More than likely, that's simple year estimates they're giving.  Thus billions.  Even if not, it's highly unlikely another .4 billion wasn't stolen before it ended (if it fact it isn't still going on).  Again, thus billions.<br />
